-Bashing, me or my fandoms, or one of my friends,
-Intolerance of all kind,

OK with that? So welcome aboard and let's have fun!!

I was too tired yesterday(and probably too excited too) to make a proper report on what happened in CDG airport when I meet the DBSK, so here is a very, very long account on how I lived that day. Be prepared, it's full of awesomeness!!!
Okay, let's begin with the beginning.
It all began when my sweet dongsaeng Carolyn left me a msn message while I was out last sunday to tell me DBSK were to arrive in our beautiful country. It was 11:30 pm when I read it, and needless to say I was so excited. It really sound unreal, I mean DBSK in France? What for? You could as well as told me it was going to rain gold. But reading soompi, it seemed more and more true, until finally , pics of them boarding came and then I knew it was definitive.
So I started to get things organized: I told
x_freya_x
 the news  on sunday but  at that time it was still dubious and she wasn't sure to come at first because her classes had started and I promised I would update her with more precise news later on. Then I asked a friend of mine who is a kind of a soulmate when it comes to fandom( we share our  KAT-TUN and Arashi love^^) if she would agree to come with me at the airport to try to meet them. What is worth mentionning is the fact thet SHE DIDN'T KNOW DBSK AT ALL. I just explained her in a rush on the phone that they were HUGE artists(and very handsome, it helped lol) and she immediately agreed to the project. I have to say I'm really thankful to her, because she went with me despite the financial cost( well the airport is rather far from Paris, the return ticket costed me 16 euros, that's quite a sum^^) and the fact she didn't know the fandom. Sophy, I love you!! but you didn't regret it, ne?!
SO, definitive news came late monday, and the flight were schedulded to land on Tuesday the 11th at 2:40pm. I was contacted at soompi by a french fellow fan, who invited me to visit the French DBSK forum( I didn't even there were a french forum for them, I only eat at soompi for Korean fandoms^^). french fans  were starting to get organized too, and after a late msn gathering monday evening, we agreed to meet at the airport at around 1:00 pm.

TUESDAY: the big day!! I was so excited I hardly got any sleep at all,and I spent my morning ironing different clothes and try them because I wanted to be at my best(how childish of me really^^). I called Sophy to tell her to bring her digital camera, and I left the house at 11:30 am to meet her in a subway station in the center of Paris at 12am(but I was already late because of all the time it took me to chose my clothes lol). I then sent Freya a sms to tell her that everything was confirmed about them coming and what their plane were due to arrive in France, and she told me she would go with us. Freya, i'm really happy you came because:

- I hadn't met you before, that was the 1st time even though we had long planned to(for our suju project lol)
-YOU TAKE THE MOST AMAZING PIC EVER!!!THAT YUNHO PIC IS JUST A PIECE OF ART!! I would marry you for the sake of this pic only^^

Freya had a very clever idea: she suggested buying red balloons to greet them, and so she did, it was a very cute idea^^
We then bought sandwiches, and took the bus for the airport.
When we arrived, some people were already waiting, approximately 8? We introduced ourselves, and it was really nice to put a face on soompi usernames. They also were a group of chinese girls, 4 or 5, and I learned later they were students from Marseille who had taken the train only to meet them in Paris. Wow, so much dedication, and they had made a banner too!!
So as time went by, the pressure began to rise. At 2:30 pm, the flight landed, and we were all waiting for them in terminal 2E. And wait we did, our hearts jumping each time the automatic doors opened, only to let out everybody except the ones we were so eager to meet. We waited until 3:30 pm(!) only to realize that the Terminal had changed: it was 2 F. Almost one hour later!! So we ran like crazy, cursing at ourselves and at the airport staff to change the terminal so randomly. No one at terminal F, so we ran (again) to terminal 2E, where someone confirmed that DBSK hadn't come out. Had they take the VIP exit? We were seriously beginning to fear that maybe we had missed them, but we decided to wait for the nest flight form Seoul, this time at Terminal 2F.
The flight landed early, 3:50pm I think instead of 4pm, and once again, our hearts began to beat like crazy. And then suddenly, some of us ran to the place when you can see people take their luggage: they were there, simply waiting. What words can I use to express the feelings I had at that precise moment? When I looked through the glass pane to see Changmin( he is so tall, It's him I clearly spotted the first), and then when I recognized Yunho, Jaejong and Yoochun? It's at that precise moment my own little ordinary universe collided with theirs I used to consider so untouchable and unreachable. Clearly, there are no words to describe that feeling. All I can tell is I had thought that if one such a thing happenned, it would be impressivelly noisy,and even messy, I mean the collision btween DBSK's realm and mine, I thought it would had been violent and almost frightening, but it was not at all like that. I was impressed that's for sure, but seeing them doing such an ordinary thing as simply fetching luggage, and looking so tired, I just understood how human they were. So now, I sure sound stupid. What I mean is, I didn't see The Gods Rising from the East, I just saw ordinary youg men who happened to achieve great thing in the music industry, and that's completely different.
So we were filming them through the glass pane and taking pics, and everybody commented on how tired they looked, obviously after a 12 hours flight. They took their luggage and played a little game of hide-and-seek with us, as they started to walk away resolutely to go to...the toilets. Ah Ah, and to think we believed they were taking some kind of VIP exit again lol
And then finally, they came out!! Needless to say screaming could be heard(not mine I swear^^).Everybody in the airport was wondering why a bunch of 20 or so girls were making such a ruckus lol .Some french people asked us, and we told them it was because of a Korean group, you should have seen their faces, their expression were priceless lol. What the heck? a Korean group? Now I think about it, trying to explain was just a lost cause. I mean I have to say, people in France are just so ethnocentrists, meaning than outside french and at best europen cultures, the others simply doesn't exist, or when they do, only in the form of prejudices and cliches. Saying you are listening to asian music, people think it's either traditional music, or the ones you can hear when you eat in chinese restaurants(old romances lol). To sum up, they looked at us like aliens lol
Back to the stars: they moved to the exit, Jae , not looking around, Yoochun;hidden behind his hoodie and cap, Changmin;tall, smiling, simply handsome, Yunho;elegant,classy,breath-taking. They was  no security at all, and when I say none, I really mean NONE. That explains all the so-close pics you can find on soompi,it was kind of disturbing, I mean I could have touch Yunho literally speaking because he was oh, so near, but it just doesn't sound right, and I was to shy anyway^^
So I have to say something: all the boys looked, and undoubtedly were tired, but Tuesday,I understood why Yunho was the leader. I'm sure he was tired too , but he was the most bright, warm of them all. Not once , he showed signs of exasperation or nervousness, he smiled at us so brightefully and genuinely. Perhaps it's the effect of admiration you could say, but although no words were said (or at least I heard none), I could sense his kindness. His attitude showed how considerate he is of fans, even though it's just 20  random girls or so. I found him simply gorgeous, tall, suave and stylish, he has a heart- melting smile, sparkling and in the meantime soft and considerate, he was dressed very stylishly and his beauty is ENTIRELY NATURAL. Trust me ladies, he has nothing to do with photoshop: THE MAN IS REAL. My favorite has always been Jae, but I may seem fickle, Yunho is my number one now I think. His attitude had been perfect all the time,and for that I'm grateful^^
Then come Changmin, my number2, because you just couldn't miss him, so tall, such a beautiful smile AND SO FREACKING GORGEOUS IT HURTS.
Next Jae: doesn't seem at ease at all, hidden behind his cap but I can't blame him, 12 hours of flight, and I understand how you can not feel at ease with fans, I was not at ease myself and I'm not even a celeb lol(come one some of them scared me^^). But no cap, no purple sweat, no blue boots (oh please Jae) can't hide his beauty, everybody sensed that, and it makes him so fragile.
Last Yoochun: too many layers boy!!Come on, share the smexiness with us...But I still love you^^
Yunho, Changmin and Yoochun signed some autographs and they went into the bus, literraly falling in their seats; Jae started to play with his DS(it seems) and we started to wave at them, they all waved back, and off they went.

Even though I wrote all those words, it's still not enough to convey the feeling. I experienced what was truely being a fan, and it was not so scary, maybe because I saw them as human, and not as deities. I mean, I used to see them as deities, they were so far above me, they were so unreal and fictional, perfect and unreachable...This airport experience brought back everything in place. I was getting slowly frustrated, fandom generates frustration anyway:you can't really know, you can't touch, you can't speak...There is alot of "can't" when you are a fan, the more when you are a fan from far away, most of us on LJ experiences that. But I saw them, young men, who were striving for their for their dreams. I saw the tiredness on their faces, the resignation and it seemed to me I saw the cost they had to pay for the amazing career they have. Of course you could say it's a nice a life, I'm sure it has its good sides, but everything comes with a price and the new reason why I admire them is because they do it with grace, joy and sincerity. They are nothing more than ordinary men, but they are accomplishing something amazing, something that few people could do, without losing their humanity. I really, sincerely, wholeheartedely  admire them for what they are achieving.
You could say I'm exagerrating, because I only got to saw them for a very limited amount of time, but really that's what I sensed from them, that's what they were emanating, at least for me.

Now I can only wish they have a nice stay, enjoying the many nice romantic places in Paris^^ In case you guys wants to know, the weather was just perfect today(Wednesday), it was bright and sunny, not too warm, not too cold, a ideal day for a photoshoot^^ I guess we will have a nice "Prince in Paris" photobook lol.
Before I leave, concerning my friend sophy who didn't know them before that fatefull 11th of September 2007, she fell in love with Yunho right away lol. A new girl to the fandom, welcome Sophy!!And thanks for being there with me^___^

Title: Black lust
Pairing: Guess who?
Rating: R for implied smut, I don't think it deserves a NC-17 rating....
Form: One-shot, very short
Genre: cracky smut(if such an expression exists )A/N: the concept is so not mine!My first time writing crack/humour fic I hope you'll like it^^ "You want me , don't you? I know you want me" Yeshung silently nodded. It was useless trying to deny it, it was true. His need was almost painful. Every fibre of his body wanted it so badly. The suave, teasing little voice resumed: "Tell me, what part of me do you like best?What do you love most in me?" It was a hard question, really.Yeshung didn't know where to start, there were so many things...Maybe the scent: a strong, masculine smell which lingered in his nose even though they weren't in the same room, a scent he could remember even in his dream. An alluring fragrance that made him drool in anticipation, like a stimulus sent to his brain to tell him great pleasure was on its way. "Or maybe it's just my look? I know black is your favorite and you love how this colour glistens and shines on me." Once again it was so true, black was so SEXY. He could never get tired of admiring him, even though it was a daily sight. But thinking about it, it wasn't the thing he liked the most. There was definitely something else, something more powerful and addictive. As if it had guessed his thoughts, the little voice said maliciously: "You don't need to tell me, I know. I knew it all along.You like my taste, you like drowning your sensual lips deep inside me." Yeshung gasped. Was it so obvious? Yes he liked his flavour, suave , rough and obsessing, a subtle blend of strength and softness. He liked how the contact tickled his tongue, the brief hesitation he had each time before decidedly taking him in his mouth, swallowing , savouring every single sip. He liked how, long after they were done, he could still feel his bitter taste. A mocking laugh: "And you are such a beast. You like it wild and rough don't you? You always take me raw." Indeed, Yeshung didn't see the use of making sweet preparations, it was just delaying the fun. What mattered was the immediate pleasure, the sensation that he was his, and his only, right here, right now. He looked at him, eyes full of lust, and slowly broke the distance that separated them, hoping to silence him at last with his lips. Someone has watched the whole scene, with a mix of shock and envy.Kyuhyun startled when he felt a hand resting on his shoulders.He turned around and saw an amused Eeteuk: "Seing your scandalized face, I believe it's the first time you catch those two in the act?" Kyuhyun nodded, too shocked to utter an answer: "You have to get used to it, it happens on a daily basis. Every member knows now, but as you joined us very recently, your reaction is perfectly normal. I hope you don't mind though." The younger boy glared at him, dumbfounded: "But Hyung, it looks so... wrong!" Eeteuk sighed, resignation written on his face: "Yes I know. But it's like a ritual, it's the same thing every morning. The first time Sungmin saw them, he was so shocked he wasn't able to utter a single word for a whole week. Can you imagine it, a WHOLE WEEK? But what can I say, Yeshung needs it, he's addicted, there's nothing we can do." A moan of pleasure escaped Yeshung's mouth, drawing their attention once again to the scene. "You'll have to wait to get your glass of milk I'm afraid.Let's give them some privacy until they're finished ok?"said the leader with a smile, going back to his room. Kyuhyun was still watching what was happening in the kitchen. He was hypnotized by the highly reprehensible acts perpetrated in the kitchen. "I wish I was this cup of coffee though"he thought, before leaving the doorstep regretfully. ********* Writing it actually made me giggle, I hope I won't be the only one ^__^ And yes, coffee has a gender and it's definitely male lol

Let me tell you :
when everyone deserts you,
when the weather sucks,
when exams is a pain in the ass,
when politic sucks,
when internet sucks(yes it happens),
when your love life sucks,

I know for sure there's something that won't EVER EVER disappoint me, and that's food.
Just see by yourself:

Really, can you imagine something more comforting than THIS?
Let me get this straight, when I say food, I mean good food, not crappy food full of sugar, fat and God knows what else, I'm french after all!(ok ok I admit sometimes carbohydrates make your life better...)
 Really, I'm a food -addict. I love going to restaurants, trying new ones and having good time with my friends, trying to snap things from their plates^^
I have this very fancy restaurant in Paris where I go when I'm loaded with money(so not very often). It's a japanese one called Azabu, and man, the food there just rocks your soul. The first pic is Magert de canard(duck breast) japanese style. You can see above the miso soup and rice. Words can't describe how good it is really. But they have another speciality:

OKONOMIYAKI!!YEAH!!
It's a kind of japanese pizza to make it simple, and it's soooo good. Just looking at it makes my mouth water...


And sometimes, when I'm broke, I cook myself and it gives THIS:


Tonkatsu(fried pork cooked in soy sauce, onions, sugar and mirin, wrapped in eggs, above rice).I swear it's me who cooked this, you can ask
coda_leia
 she witnessed me prepare it and she ate it, AND she is STILL alive !!)

And, at last, when I'm too lazy to cook, I raid my japanese-korean convenience store in Paris and I buy THIS:


Jajamyung noodles, picked radish, korean carbo-hydrates(lol), japanese bento(that day it was Teriyaki chicken).


God bless Asia fot its amazing cuisine.

Title: Be still my heart
Pairing: KangTeuk
Rating: I'm still bad at rating so let's say PG-13, ne?
Form: one-shot ,or a prologue because I'll keep writing on them.
Genre:angst?
A/N: This had been inspired by an amazing song by Silje Nergaard:"Be still my heart", I just thought it would suit Kangin's perfectly and so I commited this.Blame it on sunday and bad weather.
EDIT:here is the link to the song Be still my heart


He was stuck in one of these hours of the night, when you sense  "yesterday" has ended but you can't call it "today" yet.
Eyes staring at the ceiling which remained stubbornly invisible in the darkness.He kept repeating it in his mind, again and again the same litany.
BE STILL MY HEART.
At the moment, his heart was beating peacefully, calmly, but he wasn't trusting it anymore, he couldn't trust it anymore.
He couldn't explain since when all of this has started, or when he realized his heart was acting funny.
***********************************************

He could remember them all gathered in the living-room, all scattered, playing video games, chatting or having random mock-fights on the floor. He was the loudest of them all of course, as usual, ALWAYS, whereas Eeteuk was the quietest of them all of course, as usual, ALWAYS. A book in his hands, fliping the pages as though the world could come to an end now and he wouldn't even care.Kangin looks at him.

BE STILL MY HEART

He can hear it , beating frantically as though trying to escape the safe shelter of his own body, and he can't understand why.

And it keeps happenning, again and again.

I felt not the faintest flutter
When you brushed my cheek as you passed

No, Kangin feels nothing, he can swear it, when Eeteuk's hand lingers on his face after practise, asking him if he feels alright because he looked totally out of it.
He just feels hot because of practise.His heart is beating fast because he has trained vey hard, his knees are trembling because he is exhausted.

MY HEART BE STILL.

It has nothing to do with him anyway.He is just making things worse with his concern.Kangin can't understand why, but slowly, just the look of him makes him feel like a fish out of water, fighting to catch his breath.He is just undergoing too much stress, too much anxiety, he wants to be alone.If only he could control his heart, it would be alright, it's just a matter of time.Yes, give him more time, more days, more weeks, more months,and he'll get over it , eventually.

Days, weeks, months slowly pass, merciless, and things are just growing worse.

If our eyes should meet then so-be-it
No need to trouble a heart that's hidden
Where no-one can free it
Only to tear it apart

"Don't look at me,or I'll drown in your eyes"
"Don't smile at me, or I'll catch my breath with yours"
"Don't touch me, or you'll become my anchor"
"And then, I'll be unable to live without you, and it will be the end"
It's just thoughts that remain unsaid, in some far corner of his mind, he is not really aware of them.All he can sense is the general panic that overwhelms him for months now, and leads him to avoid Jungsu as often as possible.
He wonders if the other has noticed .Kangin acts like Eeteuk has commited the worst crime and that he doesn't want to get corrupted by it.

And maybe, in a sense, it's true.

**************************
Please, don't hate me for this, I swear I'll right happier fics in the future^^

Title: That place called home
Pairing: KangTeuk
Rating: I'm really bad new to rating so I suggest PG 13?
Form: one-shot
Genre:romance is running in my blood yeah
Summary: Why do you ask?Just read!!
A/N:So this is my first fic,I had no precise plot in mind while writing this, just wanted to set my writing mood on tracks.I ask for indulgence but constructive critiscism is good(I'll just erase you from my F-list if you don't like it^^)

Home.If you'd asked Kangin what was his defintion of home at the beginning of all of it, he'd answered:"Of course it's where my parents live, the place I grew up with my family." Yes, without a shadow of a doubt,he would have said that.
But it would have been his answer years ago.So many things had happenned in his life since then.He had left his family to live in Seoul, signed a contract with SM Ent.,met 12 others boys with whom he had trained many years, made his debut with them,experienced fame and tears.
All of this had happenned in a blink of an eye.
He felt so lost at the beginning.Of course it was a dream come true:singing, dancing, all of these were his passions, the way he found to shine.The thrill on being on stage giving his best with so many admiring and loving eyes on him...The only thought of this gave him goosebumps.But when SM officials told him he was going to be in a group with 12 other boys, he really felt disapointed.Not that he thought himself talented enough to debut alone, but 13 men?He had not enough confidence to think he had his place in the band.The members were so gifted, they were either very good singers, actors, dancers, sometimes they possessed all those qualities, and all of them were really good looking.Did he stand a chance?He was afraid of being drowned amoung them and overshadowed by such display of talents.
But those were his thoughts until he really met HIM.Thinking of it, the first time he met Eeteuk was not when he came to Seoul and were introduced by SM managers to the others boys with whom he was going to spend the years to come.Of course he saw him, vaguely, smiling softly at him while he was doing his short and somewhat embarrassed presentation in front of everyone.But it was not until the whole Super Junior project has been announced to them and Eeteuk officially appointed leader of the group that he really MET him.

It seemed to Kangin as though Eeteuk knew that were his inner thoughts at that time.Eeteuk was a really smooth leader.He was not the authoritary type.No shouting at the boys, no anger, fits or tantrums.In fact it was not necessary, everything was so natural around him.He was caring and attentive to all the members.Everyone had the feelings they really mattered for him and that was enough to be a good leader.Kangin was so admirative of how Jungsu managed softly to master the group and was genuinely loved in return.He thought himself too apart from him because he seemed he was only struggling to get the love that was so easy to Eeteuk to receive.He was feeling inferior.
But Jungsu knew better than that.Slowly,without Kangin noticing, he began to involve him in the group routine.Asking for advices, seeking his approbation,having discussions with him about the members health or how the dance training were really exhausting.All of this trifling details which helped Kangin feeling needed.Eeteuk has managed this without hurting Kangin's precious pride, that was an amazing feat indeed.
It was probably what has awoken Kangin's feelings.The suave voice calling his name,his caring glaze on him, his light touch when he was pressing his hand.Slowly, Kangin had been accustomed to touch him.He was shy at the beginning. On a particularly sweet smile adressed to him, his hand had frozen in middair in an attempt to touch his cheek, the one with the dimple that hypnotized him so much.He was slighlty trembling, but Eeteuk's smiles broadened, encouraging him, gladly accepting  with his eyes this display of affection.The throb he felt in his heart at the contact, Kangin will never forget.He wondered why on earth he waited so long to experience such softness, and if it was possible to live without it from now on.
He could now do this on a daily basis, but for him none of these gestures could equal that "first time" holiness.

Everything around Eeteuk had this natural feeling, as though it was something Kangin has known all his life.Even his scent, it was as though he had smelled it in his early childhood.It was as though he has always touched him, as though he had always kissed him.Eeteuk had in the palm of his hand that part of soul we are all after and which makes you feel complete when you find it at last.Each gaze, each smile,each touch, each whisper, each moan were telling to Kangin:"This is where you long to be, this is where you're loved, this is where you feel warm, this is where you belong".

Eeteuk was a place for Kangin, where he would find shelter when everything was deserting him, when the whole world was against him.Eeteuk would always be the place he could turn to, where he'd always been welcome.
The place where his heart belongs, Eeteuk, that place is what  Kangin now calls"home"

*****************************
That's it!So as you can see there is no real plot.This is just how I picture in my wild imagination the basis of the KangTeuk relationship.It'll help me, and the readers also to understand how those two interract in my future fics if I'm not bashed for my very very bad skills that is
Comments are love ^__^

I know someone who is very important to me, and I thought posting about that person should be a good thing to do, even though I don't really want to speak about my personnal life on my LJ, but I suppose once in a while won't hurt.
We've been friends for 3 years and now she's part of my life, I can't remenber how it was before I got to know her. I really hope for all of you you have someone like her in your life, because having a special one is such a blessing.
You know, I'm far from being an angel: I'm stubborn, egocentric, I love being the leader and takong all the decisions, I'm very obsessed when I like something and tend to ignore people's opinions and feelings when they don't go my way. Pretty bad picture, huh?But that's just the way I am and the way I live my life. Not that I am proud of it, but nobody's perfect and trying to amend me is just a real hassle sometimes. But sometimes in your life, you meet someone for whom you really want to change and improve yourself because you think: "it worths it".
She is that kind of person. I'm kind of weak, so sometimes when I am with her, even though I try very hard, I just stumble and fails and being that little dictator again. As she's been been blessed with the sweetest temper ever, she rarely says a thing to oppose me, and she never throws a tantrum. Instead, she just tells me a while after how uneasy she feels when I behave like that, and how she wishes things could be a little different sometimes. Believe me, when someone speaks to you truthfully and sincerely like that, you realize how fortunate you are to have a friend so considerate of your feelings whereas hers has been really , although uncounsciensly, ignored and sometimes hurt.
All I wanted to say is this: don't think I consider our friendship like something I selfishly own, I 'm really conscious how valuable and precious you are, and all the good things you have brought me until then. I know that if I want our friendship to last for the years to come, I'll have to fight against myself to be more considerate of your feelings. But please, bear with me and stand me a little more, because it's hard on me sometimes and you know I've lived hard things which made me afraid of being hurt. I really hope you will watch me improve and mature, and that our friendship will grow stronger as years will go by, because I think that's what Friendship is all about:growing together.
Please, stay my faithful friend
coda

No girls, rest assured, I didn't take the plane and had the time of my life with the sexiest japanese man alive that is to say Yamashita Tomohisa!!And Lord knows that's my dream, but, on a boring sunday, I just let my imagination  float around and said:"let's pretend...".
     Yes, let's pretend I live in Japan, Tokyo, let's pretend I met Yamapi while I was attending at a shounen club session, let's pretend he saw me(I know it's higly impossible but imagining this is such a bliss!!), let's pretend he asked me on a date, let's pretend I didn't die right on the spot of happiness at such an blissful demand and I gathered enough force to answer him and say yes, and finally, let's pretend the fateful day has come!!!This is my imaginary date with Yamapi, I don't want to call this a fanfiction, I just wanted to share with you  a fantasy of mine.

Tokyo, one sunday night. A girl in her late 20's in her spacious flat(those who has seen "kimi wa petto"must see what kind of flat I refer to) is rummaging in her bathroom drawers searching for lipstick and other feminine artefacts. She looks tense.
-" Oh God, he'll come at 8 and it's already 7.30!!And I'm still undressed!!I'll never survive to this date!
What am I going to wear?If only I knew where we're going... I think I'm going to put on a black skirt and a purple shirt, it's simple but cute, I don't want to be overdressed for a first date!"
Let me say here dear readers, that the heroine of this story actually looks pretty in the previous outfit!

It's 8 o' clock now. Dressed and awfully stressed, the girl is waiting in a sofa, trying to be calm but undoubtedly failling at the attempt. The bell rings.She opens the door:
-"Konbawa, Nadesico-chan, genki?
-Konbawa, Yamashita-kun, genki desu. You're perfectly on time.
-I didn't want to make you wait, and I don't want us to be late for the things I would like to do with you.By the way, you look gorgeous tonight." By saying this, he blush a little.
-"Thank you, you look very nice too"
For those who wondered what on earth Yamapi would ear on a date, here's the outfit I imagine for him:


(simple but sexy, uh?!)
-"ja! Ikouka!
-Hai! Ikkimashou!!" Nadesico feels relieved now, Yamapi has the knack to make people feel good.

Yamashita calls a cab.
-"Where are we going then?I'm sure it's going to be nice since you thought about it?
-First, I thought we could go to a nice okonomiyaki restaurant I know in Shibuya, then sing at a karaoke box in Roppongi and at last, spend the rest of the night in an amusement park. i'm sorry I decided the programm all by myself, I hope though you agree?"Yamashita looks slightly nervous.
-"Don't worry, I think it's a brilliant plan. Tanoshisou desu!(sounds amusing)"
Yamashi shows a bright relieved smile.
-"Yokatta!"

The cabs stops in Shibuya.There are a lot of people in the streets and it's a nice summer sunday evening. The night has come and people are hurrying to the subway or the buses, not paying attention to others. Yamashita and Nadesico, immersed in these crowded streets feel apart of all this turnmoil and that makes them feel more intimate.
They arrive in the okonomiyaki restaurant.
-"Have you already eaten okonomiyaki, Nadesico-chan?
-Hai. the first time was when I spend the summer holidays in Japan in 2001. then I  found a nice japanese restaurant in Paris and from time to time, I came there. I really loves this dish!
-Great you love it. Let me prepare it  for you ok?
-Thank you!"
Yamashita looks very serious while preparing the dish, (which consists in a dough with cabbage, meat on which, when cooked you put mayonnaise or worcester sauce(it's really yummy!!). To sum up, it's a kind of pizza, okonomiyaki meaning"cooked as you like"). It makes Nadesico smiles and find him cuter than ever.
-"dekita!It's ready!
-Thank you, looks delicious. itadakimasu!
-Itadakimasu!
-Oishiiiiii!!
-Maji(really)? I feel relieved, I'm not very good at this.
- Don't worry, it's really good, thank you!!
-You're welcome, I'm glad you enjoy it!"

The dinner is really great, Yamashita keeps telling amusing anecdotes about Johnny's and seeems really curious about Nadesico's surrounding.He inquires about her life in France and her studies. As she works as an English teacher, she tries to teach him some but let's face it, Yamashita is not gifted in English!!(nobody's perfect).
After dinner, they head toward a karaoke place in Roppongi. Once in the karaoke room:
-"What do you want sing," he asked
-"To begin with, i'd like you to sing me something, what do you think? You are the professionnal here!!
-Really? it's kind of embarassing, but as I was the one to suggest this place, I have to face the consequences! What do you want me to sing?
-I'd like you to sing "colorful"first, I really love this song, and do you think you can sing "daite senorita " then?"Nadesico blush a little, as this song has a special meaning for her.
- If you wish so...."
Yamashita starts to sing, eyes closed and concentrated. As the notes are filling the room, Nadesico-chan feels all the warmth and the tenderness of his voice, as if Yamashita was actually holding her in his arms. She feels secure and blessed, wishing for this moment to never end.
-"It's your turn now!! what do you want to sing?
- Err , I really don't know, it's difficult to chose" She desperately flips the pages of the karaoke book and finally finds something.
-" I think I'm going to sing "fukai mori'by Do As Infinity, it's such a beautiful and sad song.
-It's a good idea!
-But I'm not as talented as you, you'll have to be nice with me!!
-OK, ok don't worry, I won't make fun of you I promised!"
They sing for 2 hours and then Yamashita calls a cab to the amusement park.
-"I never imagined an amusement park would be so nice at night!Such things doesn't exist in France, they close usually at 8 pm
-I think it's getting more interesting at night. there are no children, it's more peaceful.
-You're right, I wish I could stay here for quite a long time, it's so nice!
-What don't we ride the big wheel before going back home? it's already 11.30 pm and the park will close at 1am.Let's make the best of it!!
-ok!"
Before that, Yamashita runs to buy 2 huge vanilla ice -cream to eat while riding the wheel.
In the cabin:
-" I really enjoyed this evening,Yamashita-kun, Your ideas were brilliant!
-really? ureshi desu!I really enjoyed it too, I don't often have the opportunity to relax on my spare time and meet the people I really want to be with. to day was precious for me"says he, looking at Nadesico straight in the eyes"I feel normal when I'm with you, and it's really valuable for me".
Both of them look through the cabin's windows. The moon shines brilliantly and silence falls. nadesico thinks it's one of these moment when you are afraid to talk , in fear words would break the magic if the moment, but she doesn't feel the need to speak. the whole cabin is filled with warmth, and she feels so special now. They don't speak for  at least 10 minutes, but their muteness is not embarassing at all because they feel deeply connected, more than how they would have been through words.

Back to Nadesico's place:
-"Yamashita-kun, I had a wonderful time today, thank you.
-Thanks to you, I had a memorable moment, I'm grateful. I hope we will have more moment like that in the future if you don't mind"added he shyly, as if he were afraid to here the answer.
-"I would be delighted too" Nadesico smiles brightly and happily" I mean it!"
-"So" Yamashita looks relieved"o yasuminasai!
-o yasuminasai!"he looks on the point to depart, but suddenly:
-"Nadesico-chan, may I ask you a favor?
-Sure." nadesico looks intrigued
-"Can I ...." not finishing his sentence, Yamashita takes Nadesico in his arms, without adding further words, and embraces tighly.After quite a long time, and which seems to short a period for Nadesico( and maybe for Yamshita himself), he mutters:
-"So, see you"
Nadesico remains speechless, as she sees Yamashita leave, and without having conscience of what she does , she manages to open her door.
She falls in the nearest sofa, wondering if she has dreamt the all evening or not, when her mobile phone rings, breaking her reverie.
She looks at it: "you've got mail"
" THANK YOUR FOR TODAY.I REALLY LOOK FORWARD TO MEETING YOU AGAIN. I THINK I ....I WILL TELL YOU THE REST NEXT TIME WE MEET.TAKE CARE. YAMASHITA"
This evening has definitely not been a simple dream.

Hello Minna!!On this beautiful sunday, I just thought I could share with you another show featuring some hotties.I'm a big Arashi fan , and it's been now 3 or months that I dl regularly tv programms such as G no Arashi or Mago Mago Arashi, because I can never get enough of them!!Concerning "mago mago Arashi" it's an 30 min long show with two arashi members visiting a remote place of Japan.Most of the time, it's on the country side and they visit elderly couple. They help them cooking, working and ask them stories about their youth and how they met and get married. I just think the concept is really sweet and funny. Yet, the programm I'm going to show you is quite diferent, as it focuses on a specific town and its touristic characteristics. It features Jun(my favorite of course!) and Sakurai, and most of the time while watching it, I was roaring of laughter! It was a kind of competition, each of them had to find by himself the best places to visit in Odawara(near Hakone). The judge is a really funny woman(I don't know her name) First challenge: finding a nice place to eat. Whereas Jun visits a really nice restaurant, Sakurai decides on a little place selling sashimis and guess what? Jun wins!!but when you look at the restaurant, you easily understand why: I love the face of Sho, sulking(as he has lost the challenge he cannot eat, poor him!!): I know, it hurts to lose!! 2nd challenge: finding the best place to visit in Odawara.Let's say it straight, Jun wins!!Let's visit a temple and do Za zen meditation: impressive , huh?! 3rd and final challenge:finding Odawara's best snack.In his attempt to find it, Jun creates a riot: and wins!!But look at that, sugoi ne?! Conclusion: look like Jun would be a better boyfriend than sakurai, he has the knack to find cool places!!I really enjoyed this show, and it was funny to look at Sakurai pouting face each time he lost! Can't resist to post Jun's pics goofing around: A big thanks to Johnny's jr clubbox, thanks to which I can dl all Arashi(and many others)shows! Makes me want to visit Japan with Jun!!

I had a thought for hamstaball today, as I mentionned on D-addict I had a tv programm featuring hayami mokomichi dating another actress, she asked me if i can put some pics there and so my dear, your wish has been granted!! First, a word of explanation. the programm is called "Hanikami", rules are simple: take two famous actors or singers, and put them in a "date situation",ie shopping in the street,wandering in public garden, having fun at a fair or anything else you would do with a boyfriend(you have to bear in mind that dating in Japan is almsot an art,there are actually magazines which focused only on this subject. If you don't know where to go for a date, they advise you romantic and original places!). All you have to then is to film the result. the one I have is with Hayami Mokomichi(Brother beat, regatta, densha otoko): pretty good, eh? He dates for the programm asami reina(Tree of heaven, Sapuri). I don't really like her because each time I see her in a drama, she's the bad one!Anyway,you can see them wandering in Tokyo streets: but the most embarassing one was when they are in a chapel, trying bride and groom outfits!!That's very cute because they look so embarassed(I was for them myself, the producers were ^pretty sadistic on this one!): I must admit he is the most handsome and maybe the sexiest groom I've seen!!here come the bride: the best is to come, Mokomichi actually cooking dinner for her!!(I wish I had a boyfriend who could do that for me!!) he is sexy with an apron!! some pics from the end of the date: To sum up, they had to tell each other their feelings about the date, and actually those were very emotionnal; i think they genuinely enjoyed spending the day with each other, and Mokomichi seems to be a very sweet and sincere man, he looked very happy.The best was he yield to her at the end"THANK YOU!!I REALLY ENJOYED THIS DATE!!" to her and she was on the verge of tears. I really enjoyed it as I am a silly romantic girl, but i can't imagine watching it starring Yamapi,it would be too painful for me!! So Hamstaball(and the others), hope you enjoyed this entry!All credit goes to the original uploader of this file at D-Addict, you can find it there. If there is no seeders,leave a comment and I will provide a link for direct download.
